<h3 class="postTitle">Summer Internship Opportunity at Sandia National Laboratories</h3>
<div class="date">April 8, 2010</div>
<div class="text"><p><strong>Job Title</strong>:  Summer Student, Undergraduate/Graduate, Software Development</p>
<p><strong>Department Description:</strong></p>
<p><span class="pslongeditbox1">The National Security Applications Department within the Geosciences Research and Applications Group provides innovative solutions to critical national security and defense problems through geoscience and geotechnology applications.  Department expertise includes development and application of technology necessary for energy and water resource discovery, recovery, conservation, protection and management.  We work with academic institutions to initiate the fundamental geoscience research on which solutions are built, and to train the next generation of geoscientists and geotechnologists.  We develop</span> new predictive modeling and simulation tools for applied problems in energy, water, environmental stewardship, and national defense.</p>
<p><strong>Required/Desired Criteria:</strong></p>
<p>Required: Upper class (summer prior to Junior or Senior year) or graduate student standing in a technical program (computer science, mathematics, statistics, engineering, physical science) at a college or university.  Knowledge (through coursework) and experience in software development within PC environments.  Experience in programming using one or more of FORTRAN, C/C++, Java, Python, Matlab.  Excellent written and oral communication skills, ability to contribute effectively within a diverse team of scientists and engineers, self motivation and creative problem solving skills.</p>
<p>Desired:  Ability and interest in development of software solutions to further goals in water and energy aspects of national security. </p>
<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>
<p>The <span class="pslongeditbox1">National Security Applications Department has an opening for an undergraduate or graduate summer student to support software development for a range of applications including: continuous realtime monitoring of water quality from field sensors, optimal sampling design for environmental restoration and renewable energy applications, geologic sequestration of byproducts of energy production and assessing the impact of climate change on infrastructure systems.  This position will support staff in the development of software tools from requirement definition through development and testing and documentation of software tools. </span></p></div>
</div>
</div></div>
